I will write Python code using the openpyxl library to extract and split the content from the "Employee Data" column into respective columns (B, C, D), while preserving the original column (A).
</thoughts>

<answer>
```python
from openpyxl import load_workbook

# Load the workbook and select the active sheet
workbook_path = "Employee_Roles_and_Ranks.xlsx"
wb = load_workbook(workbook_path)
sheet = wb.active

# Iterate through the rows in column A, extracting data
for row in range(2, sheet.max_row + 1):  # Start from row 2 to avoid headers
    data = sheet[f"A{row}"].value
    if data:  # Ensure data exists
        # Split data into First Name, Last Name, and Rank using whitespace as a delimiter
        parts = data.split(" ")
        if len(parts) >= 3:  # At least First Name, Last Name, and Rank are available
            sheet[f"B{row}"].value = parts[0]     # First Name
            sheet[f"C{row}"].value = parts[1]     # Last Name
            sheet[f"D{row}"].value = " ".join(parts[2:])  # Rank (handles multiple words)
        elif len(parts) == 2:  # Case where only First Name and Last Name exist
            sheet[f"B{row}"].value = parts[0]     # First Name
            sheet[f"C{row}"].value = parts[1]     # Last Name
            sheet[f"D{row}"].value = ""           # Rank left blank
        else:  # Case where we may have incomplete data
            sheet[f"B{row}"].value = parts[0]     # First Name
            sheet[f"C{row}"].value = ""           # Last Name left blank
            sheet[f"D{row}"].value = ""           # Rank left blank

# Save the changes to the workbook
wb.save(workbook_path)
```
</answer>
